# Lin Language TODO
# Format: [ ] pending  [/] in progress  [x] done
# Tiers: 🔴 blocking  🟡 important  🟢 nice-to-have

# Architecture reference (PIC spec):
#   pic.graph  → abstract combinator graph (γ⁺ γ⁻ δ ε ω + boundaries)
#   pic.reduce → scheduling-aware reduction ops (annihilate/dup/erase/fire_op)
#   pic.runtime→ CPU/GPU dispatch (cpu_dispatch, gpu_batch, sync_point)
#
# Node set (5 nodes):
#   γ⁺  Constructor  principal(+), aux(left, right)
#   γ⁻  Destructor   principal(-), aux(left, right)
#   δ   Duplicator   principal(*), aux(left, right)
#   ε   Eraser       principal(*), no aux
#   ω   Operation    principal(+/-), aux(inputs..., outputs...)
#
# 4 Rules: Annihilation, Duplication, Erasure, Congruence
# Rules should be mostly user-defined via a lookup table.
# Goal: CPU, GPU, and high-perf GPU shaders — unified pipeline via MLIR.

## 🔴 Tier 0 — Architecture (foundational correctness)

[/] A1. pic.reduce pass: implement reduction rules in target-independent MLIR
        - PicReduceToRuntimePass::runOnOperation() is currently a no-op {}
        - Should emit pic_reduce.annihilate / duplicate / erase / fire_op ops
          for each active pair detected in pic.graph
        - This is the CPU/GPU parity linchpin: define rules once, lower to
          both LLVM (CPU) and SPIR-V/gpu (GPU) via standard MLIR lowerings
        - Eliminates the LLVM IR builder duplication in PicRuntimeToLLVMPass
        - Marked in code with TODO(unified-pipeline)

[ ] A2. Rule lookup table (user-extensible dispatch)
        - Currently: hardcoded if-else CondBrOp chain in worker_thread
        - Should be: table keyed on (agentType_A, label_A, agentType_B, label_B)
          → pic_reduce op or user-defined rule function
        - Required for: user-defined mlir-op rules (item 4), @gpu/@cpu routing
        - GPU: same table, different lowering target
        - Goal: most rules user-defined from .lin code

[/] A3. Fix γ⁺/γ⁻ encoding for function agents
        - NODE_FN=5 / NODE_APP=6 added this PR — wrong per PIC spec
        - Per spec: function definition = γ⁺, application = γ⁻
        - They annihilate via standard Rule 1 (γ⁺ ⋈ γ⁻ → splice aux wires)
        - The "checkBeta" block is just annihilation in disguise — collapse it
        - Label encodes which function; node type encodes constructor/destructor
        - NODE_BRANCH=7 (either) should become ω(+, branch) ⋈ ω(-, branch)

[ ] A4. Boundary [ ] lowering
        - BoundaryOp declared in PicGraphDialect.td but not lowered
        - Needed for: E-graph congruence (Rule 4), effect scoping, MLIR regions
        - B1: unhandled op(+, eff) floats to outer scope automatically
        - B2: [ A ] ⋈ [ B ] → [ A ∪ B ] (boundary fusion)
        - B3: [ single normal form ] → dissolve boundary

## 🔴 Tier 1 — Language Semantics (blocking for correct execution)

[x] 1. AST_PAIR lowering in lowerExpression
